-- Barcelona Reaches Spanish Cup Final; Juventus Wins at Milan in Italian Cup
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-02-09T00:09:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/barcelona-reaches-spanish-cup-final-juventus-wins-at-milan-in-italian-cup.html
Barcelona  will face Athletic Bilbao
in the Spanish Cup soccer final after defeating Valencia, while
Juventus beat AC Milan 2-1 to open their Italian Cup semifinal.  Cesc Fabregasand  Xavi Hernandez  scored last night at the
Camp Nou stadium as Barcelona won 2-0 to complete a 3-1 victory
over the two-game semifinal. The European champion plays Bilbao
in May in a repeat of the 2009 final as it seeks a record-
extending 26th Copa del Rey title.  Juventus defender Martin Caceres scored either side of
Stephan El Shaarawy’s 62nd-minute goal at the San Siro in Milan
to give Juventus a one-goal advantage for the return game. The
other Coppa Italia semifinal is between Siena and Napoli, with
the first leg to be played today.  In  England ’s F.A. Cup, Stephane Sessegnon’s extra-time
winner gave Sunderland a 2-1 victory over Middlesbrough to set
up a fifth-round matchup against Arsenal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  